<task id="UDSS-033" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>SPA theme integration for shared components</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>4</phase>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>spa, theme, fluent</tags>
    <dependencies>UDSS-031, UDSS-032</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Ensure consistent theme handling for shared components rendered in the Power Pages SPA context. The SPA has its own theme provider — verify that shared components (DocumentUploadWizard, PlaybookLibraryShell) correctly inherit the SPA FluentProvider theme and that dark mode works in the SPA context (no Dataverse theme detection needed).</prompt>
  <role>Senior frontend developer with Fluent UI v9 theming expertise</role>
  <goal>All shared components render with correct theme in SPA context, including dark mode support</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only — no hard-coded colors; dark mode must be supported</constraint>
    <constraint source="file-ownership">ONLY touch SPA theme configuration files — do NOT modify shared library theme logic</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/theme-management.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/utils/detectTheme.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/external-spa/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Review how shared components use detectTheme() and FluentProvider — identify any Dataverse-specific theme detection</step>
    <step id="2">Verify SPA FluentProvider wraps all routes where shared components are rendered</step>
    <step id="3">Ensure detectTheme() works in SPA context (falls back to system/browser preference when Dataverse is unavailable)</step>
    <step id="4">Test dark mode toggle for DocumentUploadWizard in SPA</step>
    <step id="5">Test dark mode toggle for PlaybookLibraryShell in SPA</step>
    <step id="6">Fix any hard-coded colors or Dataverse-specific theme references</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Shared components inherit SPA FluentProvider theme correctly</criterion>
    <criterion>Dark mode works in SPA context (system preference detection)</criterion>
    <criterion>No hard-coded colors in any shared component rendering</criterion>
    <criterion>detectTheme() gracefully handles absence of Dataverse context</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
